HTML
<input type="text">
Used for single-line text input, like usernames or first names.

<input type="password">
Masks input characters for secure text input, like passwords.

<input type="email">
Validates email addresses during input (e.g., "user@example.com").

<input type="number">
Allows numeric input with optional constraints like min, max, or step.

<input type="date">
Provides a date picker for selecting calendar dates.

<input type="checkbox">
Used for selecting one or more options from a set.

<input type="radio">
Used for selecting one option from a group.

<input type="range">
Creates a slider to select a numeric value within a range.

<input type="file">
Allows users to upload files from their device.

<input type="submit">
Sends form data to the server when clicked.

CSS
1) flexbox
CSS display: flex; is a layout model that enables efficient alignment, distribution, and ordering of items within a container, even when their size is dynamic.
Container-Level Properties:
display: flex; or display: inline-flex;

Values:
flex (block-level container)
inline-flex (inline-level container)

flex-direction
Values:
row (default)
row-reverse
column
column-reverse

flex-wrap
Values:
nowrap (default)
wrap
wrap-reverse


justify-content
Values:
flex-start (default)
flex-end
center
space-between
space-around
space-evenly

align-items
Values:
stretch (default)
flex-start
flex-end
center
baseline

align-content
Values:
stretch (default)
flex-start
flex-end
center
space-between
space-around

gap
Values:
Any valid length (e.g., 10px, 1rem, 2%)


Item-Level Properties:
order
Values:
Any integer (default is 0)

flex-grow
Values:
A non-negative integer (default is 0)

flex-shrink
Values:
A non-negative integer (default is 1)

flex-basis
Values:
A length (e.g., 100px, 50%) or auto (default)

align-self
Values:
auto (default, inherits from align-items)
flex-start
flex-end
center
baseline
stretch


2) CSS GRID 
CSS Grid Properties with Possible Values
Container-Level Properties:
display

Values:
grid (block-level grid container)
inline-grid (inline-level grid container)
grid-template-rows

Values:
Lengths (e.g., 100px, 1fr, auto)
repeat() (e.g., repeat(3, 1fr))
minmax() (e.g., minmax(100px, 1fr))
grid-template-columns

Values:
Same as grid-template-rows.
grid-template-areas

Values:
Strings representing area names (e.g., "header header").
grid-auto-rows

Values:
Lengths (e.g., auto, 1fr, 100px).
grid-auto-columns

Values:
Lengths (e.g., auto, 1fr, 100px).
grid-auto-flow

Values:
row (default)
column
row dense
column dense
gap

Values:
Any length (e.g., 10px, 1rem).
justify-items

Values:
stretch (default)
start
end
center
align-items

Values:
Same as justify-items.
justify-content

Values:
start
end
center
space-between
space-around
space-evenly
align-content

Values:
Same as justify-content.
Item-Level Properties:
grid-column-start and grid-column-end

Values:
Line numbers (e.g., 1, -1)
Named grid lines (e.g., header-start)
span keyword (e.g., span 2)
grid-row-start and grid-row-end

Values:
Same as grid-column-start and grid-column-end.
grid-area

Values:
Name of an area (e.g., header)
Shorthand for grid-row-start / grid-column-start / grid-row-end / grid-column-end.
justify-self

Values:
stretch (default)
start
end
center
align-self

Values:
Same as justify-self.